Definition: based on or having the nature of an illusion
Example: illusive hopes of finding a better job; Secret activities offer presidents the alluring but often illusory promise that they can achieve foreign policy goals without the bothersome debate and open decision that are staples of democracy
Synonyms: illusory, noun, cognition, illusion, based, on, or, having, the, nature, of, an, hopes, finding, a, better, job, Secret, activities, offer, presidents, alluring, but, often, promise, that, they, can, achieve, foreign, policy, goals, without, bothersome, debate, and, open, decision, are, staples, democracy
Category: adj.all
